{"cursor":"5367","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Weapon|is_ranged=yes| |image= |caption= |name=Villar-Perosa\n|type=Submachine gun |origin= Kingdom of Italy |era= Post-WW1 |design_date= 1914\n|production_date= |service= |used_by= See users |wars= World War I |caliber= 9\nmm |part_length= |cartridge= 9 mm Glisenti |barrels= 2 side by side |feed= Box\nMagazine |action= blowback |rate=3,000 round/min |velocity= 1,050 ft/s (320 m/s)\n|weight= 6.5 kg (loaded short barreled version) |length=21 inches |variants=\n|range=1,800 m (2,200 yd) }}\n\nThe 'Villar-Perosa aircraft submachine gun' (official name 'FIAT mod. 1915') was\nan Italian double barreled light machine gun designed by Bethel Abiel Revelli, a\nMajor in the Italian Army in 1914. The weapon fired pistol calibre 9 mm Glisenti\nammunition, a reduced-power version of the famous 9 mm Para, at the extremely\nhigh rate of fire of 3,000 rounds per minute, or 1,500 rounds per minute per\nbarrel. It was arguably the first submachine gun though it was highly\nimpractical due to its design as a stationary machine gun.\n","linknr":250,"url":"Villar-Persosa_aircraft_machine_gun","recorded":1375074085,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Villar-Perosa_aircraft_submachine_gun&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Villar-Perosa_aircraft_submachine_gun&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Villar-Perosa_aircraft_submachine_gun","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bit